  "cu.titulo": "CU Scale (didactic summary)",
  "cu.p1": "<strong>Structural center (Cₛ):</strong> <code>0.000000000000000</code> is an <em>unreachable</em> ideal limit; measurable values orbit this center within ±0.000…010 ↔ ±0.999…990.",
  "cu.p2": "<strong>CU conversion:</strong> <code>(Obs − Min) / (Max − Min) × (±0.999…990)</code>. The sign (±) is chosen automatically.",
  "cu.p3": "<strong>Modes:</strong> EP (no clipping); NR (clamps to [0,1] and applies ±0.999…990).",
  "cu.p4": "<strong>Fractal reading:</strong> each decimal is a “layer” that can host a full nested scale.",

  "calc.titulo": "Step‑by‑step Calculator",
  "calc.s1": "Enter Observed/Min/Max with exactly <strong>16 digits</strong> (sign and dot don’t count). Last decimal “0”.",
